metadata.description: US Unemployment Rate | Value 01/26 | February 2026 Release

base_case.condition: What will the US Unemployment Rate be for {observation.reference_date}?
base_case.fsp_resolution: FSP equals the seasonally adjusted unemployment rate (as a percentage) for the month of {observation.reference_date}, as reported by the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics in the Employment Situation report released on {observation.release_date}. The unemployment rate measures the percentage of the total labor force that is unemployed and actively seeking employment. This data is available via the FRED API (Series ID: UNRATE).

edge_cases.condition: The U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics announces that it cannot produce the unemployment rate for {observation.reference_date} due to exceptional circumstances (such as government shutdown) but provides an alternative estimate or proxy value.
edge_cases.fsp_resolution: FSP = the alternative estimate or proxy value provided by the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics.

edge_cases.condition: The U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics announces that it cannot produce the unemployment rate for {observation.reference_date} due to exceptional circumstances and will not publish one for this period.
edge_cases.fsp_resolution: FSP = {oracle_fallback.fallback_fsp}, the most recent unemployment rate available prior to the scheduled release date of {observation.release_date}.

oracle_config.description: Prototype1 oracle configuration for US Unemployment Rate data retrieval from FRED API
